text: Eileen Robin Filler-Corn (born June 5, 1964) is an American lawyer and politician. She was the 56th Speaker of the Virginia House of Delegates from 2020 to 2022. She has been a member of the Virginia House of Delegates since 2010. She is a member of the Democratic Party. She is also the first woman and Jew to serve as Speaker of the Virginia House of Delegates. ==References== Category:1964 births Category:Living people Category:State legislators of the United States Category:Lawyers from Virginia Category:Jewish American politicians Category:Politicians from New York City Category:Politicians from Virginia Category:Politicians from Washington, D.C.
